Foxconn Technology Group will invest 
$1.6 billion in Sharp Corp. and its display unit.  Japan  is 
consuming more oil than at any time since 2008 as it seeks 
alternatives to nuclear energy. The Organization for Economic 
Cooperation and Development has called for the euro area to 
boost its bailout capacity to reassure markets. Bloomberg's 
Susan Li reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 02:32
 